{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"certifiable":true,"findings":[{"citations":[{"kind":"file","line_end":124,"line_start":113,"path":"tests/unit/test_project_portability_eval.py"}],"criterion":"An injected perfect solve returns the exact metric mapping specified in the Approach. Prove with `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_portability_eval.py -k calibration_metrics`.","detail":"test_calibration_metrics (lines 114-124 of tests/unit/test_project_portability_eval.py) asserts n_fire=4, n_nofire=4, recall=1.0, false_accept=0.0, agreement=1.0, and kappa≈1.0 — but does NOT assert stability_min or any per-case stability value. The Approach specifies the release threshold as recall 1.0, false_accept 0.0, agreement 1.0, per-case stability >= 0.6666666667, AND Cohen kappa >= 0.70; the AC requires the test to prove the 'exact metric mapping'. The stability dimension of that mapping is absent from the test. With runs=1 (the default used in the call at line 119), stability_min is trivially 1.0, so the omission does not cause a wrong answer — but the AC criterion says 'exact' and the stability assertion is simply missing.","dimension":"completion","reviewer_id":"completion-verifier","severity":"high"}],"material_fingerprint":null,"model":"anthropic:claude-sonnet-4-6","remediation":"How to resolve the unmet criteria: for each one, decide whether the work is genuinely incomplete or simply undocumented. If a requirement is already satisfied but the proof is not discoverable from the code alone, add a comment to this ticket that documents the evidence — cite the concrete artifacts that meet the requirement (file paths and line ranges, commands and their output, links, or the reasoning that ties the work to the criterion). The completion verifier reads this ticket's comments, so evidence you record there is taken into account on the next verification. For any criterion whose work is genuinely unfinished, complete it, then re-verify.","runner":"pydantic_ai","schema":"completion_verifier_fail_v1","ticket_id":"21dd-8681-4447-4bc0","verdict":"FAIL"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMPLETION_VERDICT","timestamp":1784263266372704001,"uuid":"333a568b-5201-48b8-83d2-d098e24379fb"}